Mainline Licensing Model
========================

Copyright (c) 2026 Mainline contributors.

Mainline uses a layered licensing model. The intent is to make the local
developer, agent, SDK, and protocol surfaces easy to adopt and standardize,
while keeping hosted-service infrastructure and brand rights protected.

This file describes the default licensing policy for this repository. If a
specific file, directory, package, or distribution artifact carries a more
specific license notice, that more specific notice controls that material.


Open-source local and protocol surfaces
---------------------------------------

The following areas are licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0
(SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0), unless a more specific notice says
otherwise:

- CLI core
- Agent skills, hooks, and adapters
- SDKs and libraries
- Intent Record Spec
- Agent Context Protocol

Apache License 2.0 text:
https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0


Documentation, essays, and examples
-----------------------------------

Documentation, essays, examples, tutorials, and explanatory writing are
licensed under both:

- Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International
  (SPDX-License-Identifier: CC-BY-4.0)
- Apache License, Version 2.0
  (SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0)

You may use these materials under either license.

CC BY 4.0 text:
https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/legalcode


Trademarks and brand
--------------------

The Mainline name, logo, compatibility marks, service names, and brand assets
are not open-source assets and are not licensed under Apache-2.0 or CC-BY-4.0.

Third parties may truthfully describe compatibility, for example:

- "Compatible with Mainline"
- "Implements the Mainline Intent Record Spec"
- "Works with Mainline"

Third parties may not present themselves as the official Mainline project or
service, or use names such as "Official Mainline", "Mainline Cloud",
"Mainline Enterprise", "Mainline Certified", or similar marks, without
permission from the Mainline trademark holder.


Hosted commercial surfaces
--------------------------

Hosted cloud products, the hosted GitHub App, managed PR checks, team
dashboards, hosted search, hosted indexing, analytics, and cloud
infrastructure are commercial surfaces and are not part of the open-source
distribution unless they are explicitly published in this repository under an
open-source license notice.


Local-first data boundary
-------------------------

Mainline Core is local-first. Repository data should not be sent to Mainline
Cloud unless a user explicitly connects a hosted service.


Previous versions
-----------------

This license file does not revoke rights granted for earlier published
versions under the licenses that applied to those versions.
